      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Soient $W_{n}=(X^{2}-1)^{n}, \\ L_{n}=\\frac{1}{2^{n}n!}W_{n}^{(n)}.$",
        "html": "<p>Soient <span class=\"math inline\">\\(W_{n}=(X^{2}-1)^{n}, \\\nL_{n}=\\frac{1}{2^{n}n!}W_{n}^{(n)}.\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "96c68cc7-8121-4a13-be92-9321d90fab39",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Donner le degr\\'{e} de $L_{n}$, son coefficient dominant, sa parit\\'{e},\ncalculer $L_{n}(1).$\nDonner $L_{0},L_{1},L_{2}.$",
        "html": "<p>Donner le degré de <span class=\"math inline\">\\(L_{n}\\)</span>, son\ncoefficient dominant, sa parité, calculer <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(L_{n}(1).\\)</span> Donner <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(L_{0},L_{1},L_{2}.\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "999d0393-34dc-41ef-a5dd-40db0897417d",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "D\\'{e}montrer : $\\forall n\\geq 1,(X^{2}-1)W_{n}^{^{\\prime }}=2nXW_{n},$ en\nd\\'{e}duire :\n$$\\forall n\\in \\Nn,(X^{2}-1)L_{n}^{^{\\prime \\prime }}+\n2XL_{n}^{^{\\prime}}-n(n+1)L_{n}=0.$$",
        "html": "<p>Démontrer : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall n\\geq\n1,(X^{2}-1)W_{n}^{^{\\prime }}=2nXW_{n},\\)</span> en déduire : <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[\\forall n\\in \\Nn,(X^{2}-1)L_{n}^{^{\\prime \\prime\n}}+\n2XL_{n}^{^{\\prime}}-n(n+1)L_{n}=0.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "b949b6ba-bb3a-4fa3-9a5d-36241661e22a",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer ensuite : $\\forall n\\geq 1,L_{n}^{\\prime }=XL_{n-1}^{^{\\prime\n}}+nL_{n-1},$ puis $nL_{n}=XL_{n}^{^{\\prime }}-L_{n-1}^{^{\\prime }}.$",
        "html": "<p>Montrer ensuite : <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\forall n\\geq\n1,L_{n}^{\\prime }=XL_{n-1}^{^{\\prime\n}}+nL_{n-1},\\)</span> puis <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(nL_{n}=XL_{n}^{^{\\prime }}-L_{n-1}^{^{\\prime\n}}.\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "627d12d6-3c44-4e46-a0f9-8b9d3f3d606d",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer enfin que les polyn\\^{o}mes $L_{n} $ peuvent \\^{e}tre d\\'{e}finis\npar la r\\'{e}currence :\n$$(n+1)L_{n+1}=(2n+1)XL_{n}-nL_{n-1}.$$",
        "html": "<p>Montrer enfin que les polynômes <span\nclass=\"math inline\">\\(L_{n}\\)</span> peuvent être définis par la\nrécurrence : <span\nclass=\"math display\">\\[(n+1)L_{n+1}=(2n+1)XL_{n}-nL_{n-1}.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    }
  ],
